                       int y)

getFrontWallArrangement

private GameFrame.FrontWallArrangement getFrontWallArrangement(Land[] land,
                                                               DungeonWalls frontWall,
                                                               DungeonWalls leftWall,
                                                               DungeonWalls rightWall)
Checks the front wall and surrounding walls to see what arrangement they are in. It will check to see if there is a front wall, whether there are walls surrounding it on either side, or if it is a ladder.

Parameters:
land - Land[] : the land in view
frontWall - DungeonWalls : the front wall in the given land array.
leftWall - DungeonWalls : the left wall in the given land array.
rightWall - DungeonWalls : the right wall in the given land array.
Returns:
FrontWallArrangement : the arrangement the front wall is in.

checkFrontWall

private GameFrame.FrontWallArrangement checkFrontWall(int depth,
                                                      Land[] land)
Based on the given depth, it will call the getFrontWallArrangement method with the correct set of walls. It will return the front wall arrangement so that it can be drawn.

Parameters:
depth - The depth of vision as an int.
land - The land array of the area potentially in view.
Returns:
FrontWallArrangement : The type of front wall to draw.
